                        <cell role="num">6</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Native Americans</cell>
                        <cell role="num">2</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Asian Americans</cell>
                        <cell role="num">8</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell role="num">30</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>Again, as was the case in the 1977 study, many Asian Americans were assigned to
                    East Asia, Blacks to Africa and Hispanics to Latin America. On the face, this
                    raises questions. However, when we consider such factors as open assignment,
                    personal choice, needs of the service, etc., the postings may not be too far out
                    of line from an <gloss target="#t_EEO_1">EEO</gloss> point of view. The number
                    of black personnel assigned to Europe, for instance, is in the same ball park
                    with the number of blacks assigned to Africa.</p>
